Definition: A flood event with a 1 percent chance of being equaled or exceeded in any given year (also known as a base flood).

The extent of the flood hazard for a 100-year (1 percent chance of exceedance in a given year) or 500-year (0.2 percent chance of exceedance in a given year) event, as determined by the Central Valley Flood Protection Plan, Federal Emergency Management Agency, or U.S. Army Corps of Engineers.

Term: One Hundred Year Flood (UT Division of Water Rights Glossary)
Definition: The flood having a one percent probability of being equaled or exceeded in any given year.
Vocabulary: UT Division of Water Rights Glossary

Definition: A flood event with a 0.2 percent chance of being equaled or exceeded in any given year.
